 1. What is the main difference between Excel and Google Sheet?

| Aspect | Excel | Google Sheets |
|------------|-----------|------------------|
| Type | Desktop app (Windows/Mac) | Web-based (browser) |
| Cost | Paid (Microsoft 365, ~₹500/month) | FREE (Google account) |
| Performance | Faster, handles millions of rows | Slower with large data |
| Formulas | 480+ functions, advanced analysis | 400+ functions, basic-advanced |
| Offline | ✅ Full offline | ❌ Limited offline |

Core Difference: Excel = Power tool, Sheets = Team tool



 2. Which one is better for teamwork and why?

Google Sheets 🏆 100x better for teams!

| Feature | Google Sheets | Excel |
|-------------|------------------|-----------|
| Real-time editing | ✅ Multiple users simultaneously | ❌ One at a time (or complex OneDrive setup) |
| Live chat | ✅ Built-in comments/chat | ❌ Requires Teams |
| Version history | ✅ Every keystroke tracked | ❌ Manual save versions |
| Permissions | ✅ View/Edit/Comment per user | ❌ File sharing only |
| Notifications | ✅ @mentions, email alerts | ❌ No live notifications |

Example: 5 people editing sales report → Sheets = Perfect, Excel = Nightmare



 3. Can Google Sheet work without internet?

Limited offline support:

| ✅ Works Offline | ❌ Needs Internet |
|---------------------|---------------------|
| View existing sheets | Complex formulas |
| Basic editing | Real-time collaboration |
| Simple formulas | Large datasets |
| Charts formatting | Publishing/sharing |

Enable Offline:

File → Settings → Offline → Turn on
Chrome Extension: Google Docs Offline


Excel wins: Full offline power anytime!



 4. What are the file extensions used by Excel and Google Sheet?

| Platform | Native Format | Export Options |
|--------------|------------------|-------------------|
| Excel | `.xlsx` (XML), `.xls` (old) | `.csv`, `.pdf`, `.txt` |
| Google Sheets | No local file (cloud) | `.xlsx`, `.csv`, `.pdf`, `.ods` |

Conversion:

Sheets → File → Download → Microsoft Excel (.xlsx)
Excel → Upload to Drive → Converts to Sheets




 5. How can you share a Google Sheet with others?

5 Ways to Share (Easiest → Advanced):

# Method 1: Share Button (90% cases)

🔘 Click green "SHARE" button (top-right)
🔘 Enter email addresses
🔘 Set permissions:
   ✅ VIEWER (read-only)
   ✅ COMMENTER (comments only)  
   ✅ EDITOR (full access)
🔘 Click "Send"


# Method 2: Link Sharing

🔘 Share → "Copy link"
🔘 Change to: "Anyone with link" → Viewer/Editor/Commenter
🔘 Copy & paste link


# Method 3: Add-on Protection

🔘 Protect specific sheets/ranges
🔘 "Only you" can edit critical formulas
🔘 Others see but can't break


# Method 4: Publish to Web

File → Share → Publish to web → Embed link


# Method 5: Google Workspace Admin

Domain-wide permissions
Audit logs
Access restrictions


Pro Tip: "Notify people" checkbox → Auto-email with link! 🚀



Summary: Sheets = Teamwork king, Excel = Solo power user 🏆